---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BackToSchoolCountdown from '../components/BackToSchoolCountdown.jsx';

const leftEmojis = [
	{ emoji: '🎒', size: 48, rotation: -15, top: '10%', side: '2%', delay: 0 },
	{ emoji: '📚', size: 32, rotation: 12, top: '25%', side: '8%', delay: 0.5 },
	{ emoji: '✏️', size: 40, rotation: -8, top: '45%', side: '4%', delay: 1 },
	{ emoji: '🍎', size: 28, rotation: 15, top: '65%', side: '10%', delay: 1.5 },
	{ emoji: '🎒', size: 44, rotation: -12, top: '80%', side: '6%', delay: 2 },
	{ emoji: '📚', size: 36, rotation: 8, top: '35%', side: '2%', delay: 2.5 },
];

const rightEmojis = [
	{ emoji: '✏️', size: 36, rotation: -5, top: '15%', side: '3%', delay: 3 },
	{ emoji: '🍎', size: 48, rotation: 14, top: '30%', side: '9%', delay: 3.5 },
	{ emoji: '🎒', size: 30, rotation: -10, top: '50%', side: '5%', delay: 4 },
	{ emoji: '📚', size: 42, rotation: 6, top: '70%', side: '8%', delay: 4.5 },
	{ emoji: '✏️', size: 28, rotation: -15, top: '85%', side: '4%', delay: 5 },
	{ emoji: '🍎', size: 46, rotation: 10, top: '40%', side: '2%', delay: 5.5 },
];
---

<Layout
	title="Back to School Countdown — Days Until School Starts | Clockr"
	description="Count down to your first day back at school. Enter your term start date for a live countdown showing days, hours, minutes and seconds until the big day."
	category="holidays"
>
	<div class="bts-page">
		<section class="bts-hero" aria-label="Back to school countdown">
			<div class="bts-hero-decor" aria-hidden="true">
				{
					leftEmojis.map(({ emoji, size, rotation, top, side, delay }) => (
						<span
							class="bts-float-emoji bts-float-emoji--left"
							style={`font-size:${size}px;top:${top};left:${side};--rotation:${rotation}deg;animation-delay:${delay}s`}
						>
							{emoji}
						</span>
					))
				}
				{
					rightEmojis.map(({ emoji, size, rotation, top, side, delay }) => (
						<span
							class="bts-float-emoji bts-float-emoji--right"
							style={`font-size:${size}px;top:${top};right:${side};--rotation:${rotation}deg;animation-delay:${delay}s`}
						>
							{emoji}
						</span>
					))
				}
			</div>

			<div class="bts-hero-centre">
				<div class="bts-eyebrow">
					<span class="bts-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
					HOLIDAY COUNTDOWNS
				</div>
				<h1 class="bts-hero-title">Back to School Countdown</h1>
				<p class="bts-subtitle">
					Count down to your first day back — term start dates vary, so enter
					yours below
				</p>

				<BackToSchoolCountdown client:load />
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="bts-body">
			<section class="bts-how">
				<h2 class="bts-section-title">How it works</h2>
				<div class="bts-how-card">
					<p>
						Unlike Christmas or Halloween, there is no single global "back to
						school" date. Term start dates are decided at many levels — by
						national education authorities, regional governments, individual
						school districts, and sometimes even individual schools. A child in
						one US state may return weeks before a child in another, and private
						schools often set their own calendars entirely independently of
						nearby state schools.
					</p>
					<p>
						That said, some broad patterns exist. In the UK, most state schools
						return in the first week of September, often just after the August
						bank holiday. In the United States, start dates vary enormously —
						from early August in parts of the South and Midwest to early or mid
						September in the Northeast and West Coast. Southern Hemisphere
						countries such as Australia, New Zealand, and South Africa follow
						entirely different academic calendars, with the school year typically
						running from late January or February through to December, divided
						into three or four terms.
					</p>
					<p>
						Because of this variation, Clockr does not guess your start date —
						you enter it yourself. If you are unsure of the exact date, check your
						school&apos;s website, the welcome letter or newsletter sent to
						parents, or your local education authority&apos;s published term
						dates. Once you have the date, enter it above and the live countdown
						will show exactly how long remains until the first day back.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="bts-faq">
				<h2 class="bts-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
				<div class="bts-faq-list">
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>When does school go back in the UK?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								Most UK state schools return in the first week of September,
								typically the Monday or Tuesday after the August bank holiday.
								Exact dates vary by local authority and school type — academies
								and independent schools set their own calendars. Scotland often
								returns slightly earlier, in mid to late August. Always check
								your school&apos;s website or your local council&apos;s term dates
								page for the precise date.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>When does school go back in the US?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								There is no single US back-to-school date. Start dates are set
								by individual school districts and vary widely by state — from
								early August in states like Arizona and Georgia to early or mid
								September in New York, Massachusetts, and parts of the West
								Coast. Many districts publish their academic calendars online;
								search for your district name plus "school calendar" to find
								yours.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>Why do school start dates vary so much?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								School calendars reflect local decisions about holidays, weather,
								agricultural history, teacher training days, and state or national
								regulations. In the US, education is largely decentralised — each
								district sets its own schedule. Even within one country, urban and
								rural areas, public and private schools, and different age groups
								can all start on different days.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>How do I find out my child&apos;s school start date?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								The most reliable source is your school directly — check its
								website, parent portal, or welcome pack. Schools usually send
								term dates to parents by email or post in the weeks before the
								summer break. You can also search your local education
								authority&apos;s website; most publish a full academic year
								calendar listing term start and end dates for all schools in the
								area.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>Is the school year the same in every country?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								No. School calendars differ significantly around the world. Many
								Northern Hemisphere countries run roughly September to June or
								July, while Southern Hemisphere nations such as Australia, New
								Zealand, and South Africa typically start in late January or
								February and finish in November or December. Some countries use
								a trimester system; others use two or four terms. There is no
								universal academic calendar.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
					<details class="bts-faq-item">
						<summary class="bts-faq-question"
							>Can I save or share my back-to-school countdown?</summary
						>
						<div class="bts-faq-answer">
							<p>
								You can bookmark this page in your browser to return to your
								countdown any time. Clockr does not store your date on a server —
								it stays in your browser session only. To share with family,
								send them the link to this page and they can enter the same start
								date. For a custom countdown to any date, try the{' '}
								<a href="/countdown-timer">Countdown Timer</a> tool.
							</p>
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</section>

			<div class="bts-related">
				<h3 class="bts-related-title">Related tools</h3>
				<div class="bts-related-grid">
					<a href="/days-until-christmas" class="bts-related-card"
						><span class="bts-related-name">Days Until Christmas</span></a
					>
					<a href="/business-days" class="bts-related-card"
						><span class="bts-related-name">Business Days Calculator</span></a
					>
					<a href="/countdown-timer" class="bts-related-card"
						><span class="bts-related-name">Countdown Timer</span></a
					>
					<a href="/days-until-halloween" class="bts-related-card"
						><span class="bts-related-name">Days Until Halloween</span></a
					>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.bts-page {
		width: 100%;
	}

	.bts-hero {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100%;
		padding: 72px 24px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a0a0b, #18181b);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.35);
		overflow: hidden;
		position: relative;
		min-height: 320px;
	}

	.bts-hero-decor {
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.bts-float-emoji {
		position: absolute;
		display: inline-block;
		line-height: 1;
		transform: rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		animation: bts-float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.bts-float-emoji {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}
	}

	@keyframes bts-float {
		0%,
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0) rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		}
		33% {
			transform: translateY(-10px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) - 3deg));
		}
		66% {
			transform: translateY(-5px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) + 3deg));
		}
	}

	.bts-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
	}

	.bts-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.bts-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3b82f6, #facc15);
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.45);
	}

	.bts-hero-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 64px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3b82f6, #facc15);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.bts-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0 0 28px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-widget) {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
	}

	:global(.bts-input-section) {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 420px;
		margin-bottom: 8px;
	}

	:global(.bts-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		width: 100%;
	}

	:global(.bts-input-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
	}

	:global(.bts-input) {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 280px;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 600;
		text-align: center;
		color: #fff;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.35);
		border-radius: 12px;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.bts-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(250, 204, 21, 0.6);
	}

	:global(.bts-input::placeholder) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	:global(.bts-input-note) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 12px 0 0;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.bts-results) {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		margin-top: 20px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown) {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-end;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px 12px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-block) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-num) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3b82f6, #facc15);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		min-width: 64px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-num--days) {
		font-size: clamp(80px, 13vw, 120px);
		letter-spacing: -4px;
		min-width: 100px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-sep) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 26px;
		padding: 0 2px;
	}

	:global(.bts-countdown-unit) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	:global(.bts-target-date) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(15px, 2.5vw, 18px);
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 24px 0 0;
